cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "txtdown: Minimal markup for Latin text collections"
abstract: >-
  txtdown is a human-readable plaintext markup format for scholarly
  collections of Latin (and other classical) texts, with inferrable
  hierarchical structure for citation, direct-speech and cross-source
  quotation, and tolerance for inline TEI/XML tags that still yields
  clean plaintext for NLP.
type: software
authors:
